WEBVTT

00:00:01.490 --> 00:00:06.730
The account from which the words of today's scripture text is drawn

00:00:09.769 --> 00:00:12.970
really are the scriptural introduction to these two women

00:00:14.250 --> 00:00:16.250
Mary and Martha

00:00:16.929 --> 00:00:18.929
What do we know about them?

00:00:19.089 --> 00:00:25.969
Well, they were siblings and they were both women of faith disciples of Christ and

00:00:26.530 --> 00:00:28.530
and each had a unique

00:00:28.530 --> 00:00:33.649
personality and outlook. That's not unusual in families, is it?

00:00:34.609 --> 00:00:45.090
Now we can imagine their excitement in the late summer or early autumn of the year 32 CE as they prepared their home for a very

00:00:45.649 --> 00:00:47.649
special guest

00:00:48.289 --> 00:00:55.369
Jesus the Son of God. Can you imagine what it would be to have Jesus visit your home?

00:00:56.929 --> 00:00:58.929
Well, when Jesus arrived

00:00:58.929 --> 00:01:04.530
Martha was busy with preparation, but Mary chose to sit at Jesus' feet and

00:01:04.890 --> 00:01:08.329
the account tells us that she kept listening and

00:01:10.780 --> 00:01:15.579
Martha was a product of her upbringing. In first century Jewish life,

00:01:16.219 --> 00:01:20.019
women were taught to care for domestic duties.

00:01:20.620 --> 00:01:26.219
So her frustration with her sister reached a breaking point, didn't it?

00:01:26.859 --> 00:01:30.859
And we can read about it in Luke chapter 10. Turn there with me, please.

